  saturated fat: 33 g
  carbohydrates: 43 g
  sugar: 6 g
  protein: 25 g
  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 1550 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/loaded-baked-potato-soup-654a9e5533e8a37769159abd
time required: 35 minutes
course: main course
servings: 2
cuisine: North America
---

Wash and dry produce. Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Trim and
thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

In a large #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine potatoes with half the
@garlic powder{1%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest later); season generously with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss until potatoes are evenly coated.

Cover tightly with #plastic wrap{}; microwave until tender, ~{6-7%minutes}.
Keep covered until ready to use in Step 5.

Meanwhile, heat a large dry pan over medium-high heat. Add @bacon{4%ounce}; cook,
turning occasionally and adjusting heat if browning too quickly, until crispy,
~{6-10%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer bacon to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Reserve bacon
fat in pan (you'll use some of it in the next step). Once bacon is cool enough
to handle, roughly chop.

In a large #pot{}, combine scallion whites, remaining garlic powder,
@butter{1%tablespoon}, and 1 TBSP reserved bacon fat (2 TBSP bacon fat and 2 TBSP
butter for 4 servings) over medium-high heat. Cook, stirring, until scallion
whites are tender and fragrant, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Add @cream sauce base{4%ounce}, @chicken stock concentrate{2}, and 2 cups
water (4 cups for 4); bring to a boil.

In a small #bowl{}, combine half the @cornstarch{1%tablespoon} and ½ TBSP water
(all the cornstarch and 1 TBSP water for 4 servings). Whisk until smooth.

Once potatoes are done, add to pot along with cornstarch mixture and cook,
stirring occasionally, until soup has thickened, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Reduce heat to low. Add @white cheddar cheese{1/2%cup} and half the chopped
bacon to soup; stir until cheese is melted and combined.

Divide soup between #bowls{}. Top with @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup},
@sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}, scallion greens, remaining chopped bacon, and as
much @hot sauce{1%teaspoon} as you like. Serve.

> Bacon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.